# BDD Step Definitions Skill (Cucumber + Java + Playwright)

## Project Stack Assumptions
- **Test Framework**: Cucumber 7.x with JUnit 5
- **Browser Automation**: Playwright for Java
- **Pattern**: Page Object Model (POM)
- **DI**: PicoContainer or Spring (ask user if unknown)
- **Step Definition Location**: `src/test/java/stepdefinitions/`
- **Page Objects Location**: `src/test/java/pages/`

---

## Step Definition Rules

### 1. Annotations
Use correct Cucumber annotations from `io.cucumber.java.en.*`:
```java
import io.cucumber.java.en.Given;
import io.cucumber.java.en.When;
import io.cucumber.java.en.Then;
import io.cucumber.java.en.And;
```

### 2. Class Structure
```java
package stepdefinitions;

import io.cucumber.java.en.*;
import pages.LoginPage;
import org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;

public class LoginSteps {

    private final LoginPage loginPage;

    // Inject via constructor (PicoContainer DI)
    public LoginSteps(PlaywrightContext context) {
        this.loginPage = new LoginPage(context.getPage());
    }

    @Given("the user is on the login page")
    public void userIsOnLoginPage() {
        loginPage.navigateTo();
    }

    @When("the user enters username {string} and password {string}")
    public void userEntersCredentials(String username, String password) {
        loginPage.enterUsername(username);
        loginPage.enterPassword(password);
    }

    @Then("the user should see the dashboard")
    public void userSeesDashboard() {
        Assertions.assertThat(loginPage.isDashboardVisible()).isTrue();
    }
}
```

### 3. Parameter Types
| Gherkin Syntax | Java Type |
|---|---|
| `{string}` | `String` |
| `{int}` | `int` |
| `{double}` | `double` |
| `{word}` | `String` (no spaces) |
| `{boolean}` | `boolean` |
| DataTable | `io.cucumber.datatable.DataTable` |

### 4. DataTable Example
```java
@When("the user fills the form with:")
public void userFillsForm(DataTable dataTable) {
    Map<String, String> formData = dataTable.asMap(String.class, String.class);
    page.fill("#name", formData.get("name"));
    page.fill("#email", formData.get("email"));
}
```

### 5. Hooks
```java
import io.cucumber.java.Before;
import io.cucumber.java.After;
import io.cucumber.java.Scenario;

public class Hooks {

    @Before
    public void setUp(Scenario scenario) {
        // runs before each scenario
    }

    @After
    public void tearDown(Scenario scenario) {
        if (scenario.isFailed()) {
            // take screenshot on failure
            byte[] screenshot = page.screenshot();
            scenario.attach(screenshot, "image/png", "failure-screenshot");
        }
    }
}
```

