## Naming Conventions
- Step definition class name: `<Feature>Steps.java` (e.g., `LoginSteps.java`, `CheckoutSteps.java`)
- Method names: camelCase, describe the action (e.g., `userClicksSubmitButton`)
- One class per feature area, not one class per step
- Keep business logic in Page Objects, not in step definitions

---

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
- ❌ Don't write Playwright locators directly in step definitions — use Page Objects
- ❌ Don't hardcode URLs — use config/properties file
- ❌ Don't use `Thread.sleep()` — use Playwright's built-in auto-wait or `waitFor*` methods
- ✅ Keep steps readable like English sentences
- ✅ Reuse existing steps — don't duplicate

